# Code Explanation — ThrustStand.ino

This document walks through the entire sketch section by section so you understand what every part does and why.

---

## Libraries
```cpp
#include <WiFi.h>
#include <WebServer.h>
#include "HX711.h"
```

- **WiFi.h** — built into the ESP32 core. Used to create the wireless access point.
- **WebServer.h** — built into the ESP32 core. Handles HTTP requests from the browser.
- **HX711.h** — third party library by Rob Tillaart. Handles communication with the HX711 load cell amplifier chip.

---

## Configuration constants
```cpp
const char* AP_SSID = "ThrustStand";
const char* AP_PASS = "thrust1234";

const int HX_DT  = 4;
const int HX_SCK = 5;

float counts_per_lb = 206000.0;
```

- **AP_SSID / AP_PASS** — the WiFi network name and password the ESP32 broadcasts. Change these if you want a different network name or password.
- **HX_DT / HX_SCK** — the GPIO pins the HX711 data and clock lines are connected to. These must match your physical wiring.
- **counts_per_lb** — your calibration constant. This is the number of raw HX711 counts that equals one pound of force. This value comes from the calibration procedure and is the only number you change when re-calibrating.

