## Sample struct and readSample()
```cpp
struct Sample {
  float thrust_lb;
  float thrust_lb_raw;
  long  counts;
};

Sample readSample() {
  long counts = scale.read_average(3);
  long offset = scale.get_offset();
  float thrust_raw = (counts - offset) / counts_per_lb;
  float thrust = thrust_raw;
  if (thrust < 0.0f && thrust > -0.20f) thrust = 0.0f;
  ...
}
```

- **read_average(3)** — reads 3 samples from the HX711 and averages them. Using 3 samples is a balance between speed and noise reduction.
- **get_offset()** — returns the tare zero point set during setup or when the Tare button is pressed.
- **(counts - offset) / counts_per_lb** — subtracts the zero point then divides by the calibration constant to get pounds.
- **The clamp** — values between -0.20 and 0 are snapped to 0. This prevents tiny noise from showing as negative thrust at idle. Real negative values (larger than -0.20) are kept so you can see them for debugging.
- **thrust_lb_raw** — the unclamped value, shown in the Raw card on the dashboard. Useful for diagnosing calibration issues.

