## Stopwatch logic
```js
if(j.thrust_lb > 0.25 && !swStarted){ swStart(); }
```

- The stopwatch does not start on page load.
- It starts automatically the first time a thrust reading exceeds **0.25 lb**.
- The 0.25 lb threshold prevents vibration and noise at idle from accidentally starting the timer.
- Pause freezes the elapsed time. Resume picks up from where it left off.
- Reset returns to 00:00.0 and waits for the next thrust event.
- Tare and Clear both reset the stopwatch automatically.

---

## CSV logging

Every reading is appended to a string in RAM:
```
time_s,thrust_lb
0.50,0.000
1.00,2.341
1.50,3.102
```

- The log is trimmed when it exceeds 60,000 characters (roughly 3,000 readings) to prevent running out of RAM.
- Clicking Download CSV fetches `/csv` which the ESP32 sends as a file download.
- The log is lost when the ESP32 is powered off. Always download before unplugging.

