## setup() and loop()
```cpp
void setup() {
  scale.begin(HX_DT, HX_SCK);
  scale.set_gain(128);
  scale.tare(30);
  WiFi.softAP(AP_SSID, AP_PASS);
  server.begin();
}

void loop() {
  server.handleClient();
}
```

- **set_gain(128)** — sets the HX711 to Channel A at 128x gain. This is the standard setting for a 350 ohm load cell.
- **tare(30)** — takes 30 readings at startup to establish the zero point with no load on the cell.
- **loop()** only calls `handleClient()`. All the work happens inside the HTTP handler functions when the browser makes a request.
